content:
Configure Coverages

After you add coverages to a root product spec, you can configure them as child coverages, modify their attributes, make them optional, add rules to optional coverages, and re-order them in the UI.

Make Coverages Optional
Select Optional on the coverage to make it optional.

Re-order Coverages
Drag and drop coverages in the order you want them displayed on the UI when users see the product.

Optional Coverage Rules
Set up rules that apply to optional coverages on Insurance products.

Set Up Coverages as Children of Insured Items for Multi-Instance
Associate coverages with an insured item after adding them to a root product spec.

Modify and Sort Attributes on Coverages
Change configuration attributes in a coverage on a root product spec.
title: Configure Insurance Product Coverages
